                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you about the above-named 40-year-old female patient who was admitted to our department on 11.12.2018 for elective surgical sterilization following her voluntary request for permanent contraception. Pre-operative assessment including routine blood work, clinical examination, and anesthetic evaluation was performed and revealed no contraindications to the planned procedure. Informed consent was thoroughly documented. On 12.12.2018, bilateral tubal ligation was successfully performed under general anesthesia without intraoperative or postoperative complications. The postoperative course was uneventful. The patient was discharged home in good general condition on 12.12.2018. She has been counseled regarding the permanent nature of the procedure and post-operative care instructions. Please continue routine follow-up care. Should any concerns arise, please do not hesitate to contact us.</div>"
            },
